The Telegraph - Calcutta : Bengal

 BRIEFS

 Calcutta, Feb. 17: Norwegian scientist Tirje Lillehaug was robbed of his wallet and two expensive cameras by two youths who had posed as guides and accompanied him to Victoria Memorial and the planetarium. 

 Mohammed Ali alias Krishna, 26, and Brian Ferguson, 24, who are fluent in English, German and French, were caught in a Garia slum today. 

 Calcutta: A security guard at a Sarat Bose Road housing complex has been arrested in connection with a taxi drivers death after a row over parking. Sujoy Saha had asked Ashok Sahu not to park in front of the complex. A scuffle followed and Sujoy pushed Ashok to the ground. Sujoy took him to hospital, which discharged him after treatment. But Ashok died later.

 Howrah: Relatives of a Howrah resident alleged that he was brutally beaten in the Bally police station lock-up. Ajay Yadav, 25, of Lilu-ah had been accused of torturing his wife.

 Santiniketan: Three pilgrims from Murshidabad died after they fell off the roof of a bus heading to a fair near Tarapith.




